## 4. Routing System

### 4.1 Asset Serving Route
**File:** `Admin/app/Modules/Authentication/Routes/auth.php`

**Purpose:** Serve module assets directly during development without publishing.

**Route Pattern:**
```php
Route::get('/modules/authentication/{type}/{file}', function ($type, $file) {
    // Serves files from assets directory
})->where('type', 'css|js|images')->where('file', '.*');
```

**Supported Asset Types:**
- CSS files
- JavaScript files
- Images (webp, png, jpg, jpeg)

**MIME Type Mapping:**
```php
$mimeTypes = [
    'css' => 'text/css',
    'js' => 'application/javascript',
    'webp' => 'image/webp',
    'png' => 'image/png',
    'jpg' => 'image/jpeg',
    'jpeg' => 'image/jpeg',
];
```

**Benefits:**
- No need to publish assets during development
- Automatic file serving
- Proper MIME type headers
- 404 handling for missing files

### 4.2 Authentication Routes

#### Guest Routes (Unauthenticated Users)
```php
Route::middleware('guest')->group(function () {
    // Login
    Route::get('/login', [AuthController::class, 'showLogin'])->name('login');
    Route::post('/login', [AuthController::class, 'login']);
    
    // Two-Factor Challenge
    Route::get('/two-factor-challenge', [TwoFactorChallengeController::class, 'show'])
        ->name('two-factor.login');
    Route::post('/two-factor-challenge', [TwoFactorChallengeController::class, 'verify']);
});
```

#### Authenticated Routes
```php
Route::middleware('auth')->group(function () {
    // Logout
    Route::post('/logout', [AuthController::class, 'logout'])->name('logout');
    
    // Two-Factor Setup
    Route::get('/user/two-factor-authentication', [TwoFactorAuthController::class, 'show'])
        ->name('two-factor.setup');
    Route::post('/user/confirmed-two-factor-authentication', [TwoFactorAuthController::class, 'confirm'])
        ->name('two-factor.confirm');
    
    // Recovery Codes
    Route::get('/user/two-factor-recovery-codes', [TwoFactorAuthController::class, 'showRecoveryCodes'])
        ->name('two-factor.recovery-codes');
    Route::post('/user/two-factor-recovery-codes', [TwoFactorAuthController::class, 'regenerateRecoveryCodes'])
        ->name('two-factor.recovery-codes.regenerate');
});
```

